<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/24394370-chip-howell"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1380701238i/24394370._UY100_CR11,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/24394370-chip-howell">Chip Howell</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No. It&apos;s not a traditional book. If you feel a sense of confusion and disorientation, that&apos;s the point. No spoilers, but the longer stories/novels are<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No. It's not a traditional book. If you feel a sense of confusion and disorientation, that's the point. No spoilers, but the longer stories/novels are recursive in that they may (or may not) feature the same characters in different roles. The whole book is open to interpretation.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
